items.name: Dynamic Poses
items.description:
Dynamic Poses Package

Presenting the Dynamic Pose Package, a collection of poses meticulously crafted for seamless integration with both ControlNet and the OpenPose Editor. This package offers an array of expressive poses that can effortlessly be employed, enhancing the visual appeal and interactivity of your projects.

Requirements

Make sure you have the following installed:

  • ControlNet + OpenPose model (For a written tutorial click here).

Optional

  • OpenPose Editor (See here how to install & download)

Included in Downloads

The following is included when you download the poses:

  • Preview of Pose

  • JSON file of Pose

  • Stick figure of Pose

Additionally there is a "presets.json" file with all poses in JSON format.

How to use?

To use with ControlNet & OpenPose:

Drag & Drop the Stick Figure Poses into a ControlNet Unit and do the following:

  • To enable ControlNet, simply check the checkboxes for "Enable" along with "Pixel Perfect".

  • Select "OpenPose" as the Control Type

  • Select "None" as the Preprocessor (Since the stick figure poses are already processed)

  • Select "Control_v11p_sd15_openpose" as the Model

To use with OpenPose Editor:

For this purpose I created the "presets.json" file, which can be found in the downloaded zip file. You can place this file in the root directory of the openpose-editor folder within the extensions directory:

The OpenPose Editor Extension will load all of the Dynamic Pose Presets from the "presets.json" file. You can then choose a pose from the Presets dropdown menu, and by clicking "Load Preset", you'll be able to preview the selected pose. From there you can send it to either "txt2img" or "img2img".

My Settings

For the creations of the preview images inside the downloads folder I used the following settings:

Example Preview Image:

  • Positive Prompt: ((detailed)), ((masterpiece)), ((best quality)), ((Astounding)), ((Enchanting)), (Striking), woman, (lara croft:1.2), (tomb raider:1.2), (tomb:1.1), natural light inside tomb, jungle, plants in background, (detailed face:1.2), clear skin, (cleavage:1.1), perfect light, perfect shadows, <lora:3DMM_V12:0.6>, <lora:add_detail:0.7>

  • Negative Prompt: (worst quality:1.2), (low quality:1.2), (lowres:1.1), (monochrome:1.1), (greyscale), multiple views, comic, sketch, (((bad anatomy))), (((deformed))), (((disfigured))), watermark, multiple_views, mutation hands, mutation fingers, extra fingers, missing fingers, watermark

  • Sampling Steps: 30

  • Sampler: DDIM

  • CFG scale: 7

  • Model: reV Animated

  • LoRa's: 3DDM & Detail Tweaker

At times, I also used the ADetailer Extension to improve the quality of the faces.

More Poses Coming Soon?

These Dynamic Poses are just the starting point for our package. Stay tuned for more uploads as I'll be continually expanding the selection to offer you a broader array of options. Feel free to share your insights in the comments, and I'll gladly integrate your suggestions into the growing collection.

Latest Tutorials

To access the most up-to-date tutorials, make sure to visit our website and explore our YouTube channel. Don't hesitate to explore these resources for the latest guidance and insights.

  • Next Diffusion Youtube Channel

  • Next Diffusion Website

Thanks for the support and happy generating â¤ï¸

items.name: Kilmaria [Isekai One Turn Kill Nee-san / My One-Hit Kill Sister]
items.description:
The charmingly chaotic demon Kilmaria from the anime series. "KA KA KA" not included (unfortunately).

How to use
Use the trigger word "kilmaria" to start with. Depending on the model and style modifiers active you may want or need to use "grey eyes", "horns", "pointy ears", "very long black hair" and so on.
Her default outfit is tagged as "pantyhose, navel, bare shoulders, cleavage, fur trim, detached sleeves, clothing cutout, purple dress, white cloak, cross-laced footwear, ascot". You may need to use some of these in negatives if you want to prompt her in something else, "ascot", "fur trim" and "detached sleeves" usually being the most common.
For more prompting tips please see the sample images or the uploaded zip of training tags.

Misc
There are other releases available for this character, this one is trained on NAI which may work better for some. Tested on AOM2 and AOM3.
Dataset of 27 screencaps trained at 512 resolution. Two were "demonfied" versions of her human form in order to improve dress-up versatility a bit (you're not just prompting her naked are you right, right??)
All images are untouched txt2img upscaled, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LyCORIS is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material.

items.name: VrChat Diffusion (VrChat Style LORA)
items.description:
Trained with many images of in game selfies and screen shots, for all you VR nerds but we all know beat saber is better

The models I make are tested for resolutions under 512 (Not by choice), results may be different (Probably better) with higher resolutions. Ref images are in the lower quality as well.

Honestly, donate a penny and I'd be happy
Ko-fi: https://ko-fi.com/keyennorman

Prerequisites, straight to the point, quite a bit to go over

1. Wights fluctuate quite a bit. I've tried from 1 to 0.5 etc and it seems like all of them COULD work under the right circumstance BUT I'd recommend starting with 0.7-1
2. This LORA is large for a reason, wanted to make sure the style was correct and fool proof, maybe in the future I can update the model to a more optimized state but for now you better have a spare USB or memory card laying around somewhere, loser
3. As for other LORA capability there is potential, I encourage you to experiment to see which LORAs work the best with this model.
4. I find the style struggles with male bodies as well as basic actions such as HOLDING. But that's to be expected in all honesty. Maybe it was just me who had the problem.
5. Probably can generate futa images, for you cultured folk. I haven't tried it myself.

Hopefully your experience with this model proves fruitful in some way, cheers.

items.description:
Miao Ying, Cathay dragon impales a blue mutant raven on a jade rod and makes warp soup out of it. Fist blow!

NSFW Model

LoRA was trained on Animefull due to best compitability with all anime / 2.5D checkpoint models.

0.75 - 0.85 strength of Lora is the best radius (For combining with other LoRAs, I recommend reducing weight).

Clip skip 2.

Some necessary tokens for better experience:

MiaoYing, mature female, solo,

white hair, long hair, high ponytail, lipstick, makeup, detailed hair, detailed face, blue eyes, glowing eyes, bright pupils,

For casual battle dress (close to vanilla):

horned headwear, armored dress, breastplate, (single gauntlet:1.1), long dress

Also in negative: thighs, nude, pelvic curtain

For sexy battle dress (close to lazy mod for WH3:TTW):

horned headwear, armored dress, (single gauntlet:1.1), cleavage cutout, fishnet thighhighs, high heel boots, large breasts, cleavage

For alt. sexy dress:

horned headwear, highleg dress, high heels

If you want remove her headwear just at it in negative.

Extra info! I recommend you next prompt order for NAI-based mixes (you can see it in my preview arts):

  1. (highres, high quality:1.3) ("masterpiece" and "8K" kill some concepts. Be careful if you try some difficult clothes or concepts.

    Also other lighting / shadows / sharpness / fov / colorful if you need effects are here. Sometimes it doesn't work if style of anime or game was baked in LoRA.

  2. Activation word (from lora civitai page, usually character name), what character is doing (with details), char expressions, camera position, background;

  3. Hair details, face details, jewelry, crowns, hats, etc.

  4. Clothes and shoes; Or nude, naked.

  5. Body details (large breasts, cleavage). Genitals if you want generate it.

Also LoRA trained with some NSFW poses. So you can try it with LoRAs or without it.

Advices for better experience:

items.name: Sailor Senshi Uniform
items.description:
In the name of the moon, I'll punish you!

Dress your characters up in their own Sailor Senshi attire. Works suprisingly well with most character LoRA, allowing you to dress up your favorite characters at will.

Does not work as well on realistic models, but you can get some good results with a lot of patience and good prompting.

Main tag is sailor senshi uniform. To strengthen the effect you can also use some reinforcing tags like pleated skirt, bow, brooch, leotard, etc. but for the most part it's not necessary. You may also find that unprompted hairstyles tend to drift toward the iconic Usagi bangs and odango... you can avoid this by combining with specific hairstyle or character LoRA, or with heavy prompting. It was virtually impossible to train these default hairstyles out enough as the base SD model is very familiar with Sailor Moon and seems to make a lot of it's own connections.

Enjoy!

items.name: Madeline Smith (1970-75 era - LoRA)
items.description:
LoRA of UK actress Madeline Smith, who was one of the most ubiquitous British faces of the 1970s, featuring in a number of films and TV programs of the era.

Uses 114 ref images and 1989 (real) reg images, trained for 12,000 steps at a batch size of 1, using BF16 on a 3090, with a training time of four hours.

Though this model uses the same data as my previous Madeline Smith checkpoint, it is not a Kohya extract from a DreamBooth model, but was trained from scratch in Kohya, after a lot of manual annotation of images.

It's fairly well disentangled, compared to the old checkpoint and checkpoint>LoRA extractions that I put up, and quite flexible - but please keep the CFG very low (about 3.5 - and usually it's best to keep the sampling steps low too, unless inpainting), and the LoRA strength at about 0.8.

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

This model may well produce subject-accurate NSFW output unless countered in negative prompts.
